Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. Unroll dough on cookie sheet; starting at center, press out dough into 14x12-inch rectangle. Brush dough with olive oil; bake 7 minutes. Spread sauce over crust; top with mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese and pepper flakes. Arrange pepperoni in spiral shape in center of pizza (see photo). Bake 10 to 13 minutes longer or until crust is deep golden brown and cheese is melted and bubbly. To serve, cut pizza into 4 rows by 4 rows, making 16 pieces.